Students and instructors will purchase $5 movie tickets. Each student and professor are prepared to pay $5 and $10, respectively. 900 students and 100 professors will each purchase one ticket, selling 1000 tickets. The movie theater's profit is ticket sales minus expenditures. 1000 $5 tickets get $5000. The total cost is $3000 since each ticket costs $3. Thus, the theater's profit is $2000. Consumer surplus is the gap between consumers' maximum price for an item and their actual price. Students' consumption surplus is $0 while professors' is $500. 